Show HN: A daemon for writing Telegram bots in shell CGI style
text: I found there were a number of things that I wanted a personal telegram bot to do which would have been relatively difficult or annoying to implement in a full-blown programming language, but pretty easy to string together a shell script for. So I wrote this program that acts sort of like a classic CGI gateway for Telegram conversations, forwarding messages over stdin/stdout.

Ask HN: Will AI change core education?
text:
With the ability to train models omitting certain parts of an education curriculum I would think it will become increasingly more objective how much some of the more controversial parts of our core educational system exists.

E.g, does a model trained with classical literature really outperform other models that omit it in things like creativity?

Ask HN: Have you found any LLM powered accounts on social media yet?
text:
Asking because I'm starting to feel like the predictions of LLM generated content flooding social media are about to come true.

I've spotted two obvious spam accounts on Reddit within the past day. Both had comments in many many different subreddits, within minutes or each other, all in a very GPT style of speech. I tried submitting a link to one as a post here but it got flagged, so I'm not sure if linking to it is against the rules.

What's also interesting is that the accounts were able to respond to images, so I'm guessing it's GPT-4 powered.
